body:
Hi,
If you inspect the file train.py, you can see that the argument --transfer does not exist anymore.

You can retrain from existing weights by specifying the weights as arguments, for example:

`python train.py --cfg cfg/yolov3.cfg --data data/xx.data --weights weights/yolov3.pt`

You can also implement transfer learning, see [https://pytorch.org/tutorials/beginner/transfer_learning_tutorial.html#](url)

@sdoloris When I use the weights argument, but my own cfg file (I was to train with pretrained weights, to detect only 2 classes) I get an error that the weights file isn't compatible with the cfg. Any suggestions?

@glenn-jocher Thanks a lot. I've tried training, with yolov3-spp.pt but I got the same incompatible error. Does it have to be with yolov3-spp-ultralytics.pt? I'm downloading it now and trying that too, just in case. 

Edit: After running again with yolov3-spp-ultralytics.pt I still get the error. I'm copying it below.

python3.6 train.py --data data/Project/proj.data --cfg cfg/Project.cfg --weights weights/yolov3-spp-ultralytics.pt --img-size 960 --rect --batch-size 2 --accumulate 32 --epochs 50

![yoloerror](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/40172212/78187135-91d77180-7476-11ea-9f01-5dfa3c99696c.PNG)
Then your cfg is incompatible with pretrained weights. You can train from scratch instead: --weights ‘’

@glenn-jocher  I was hoping to use transfer learning, since my dataset is rather small. Is there no way to load only the first layers of weights (those that my cfg shares with the yolov3 cfg) and train the rest from scratch? I'm not quite sure how to work with the .pt files.

Thanks in advance for the help!

@JerAnsel it's already tried to load the first layers, but your cfg is different so it cant, this is what it is telling you already in the error message.

If you only modify the class count according to the tutorial then everything will work correctly. See https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3/issues/192

@glenn-jocher The only thing I've changed in the cfg is the class count in each yolo layer to 2, and the filters in each preceding layer to 21 just as it says in 192, and in the wiki. Everything else in the cfg is the way I got it from the repo.

@JerAnsel if you only change the class count then everything should be fine. Be careful though, yolov3.cfg is different from yolov3-spp.cfg.

The yolov3-spp-ultralytics.pt file corresponds to yolov3-spp.cfg, so you need to use yolov3-spp.cfg as the basis for your modifications. If you only change the class count then everything should work fine.
@glenn-jocher Thanks a lot! I really appreciate the help. I'll try it out and get back to you.
